headline: Tesla Stock Looks Weak Heading Into Earnings. Blame AI.
summary: Tesla stock was down 2% on Wednesday afternoon, ahead of the company reporting third-quarter results, which are due out after the market close.  Shares of GE Vernova stock were off 2.3% in late trading at $571.85 after the power equipment supplier reported better-than-expected earnings.  It’s been a wild day for that stock: GE Vernova shares traded as high as $610 a share and as low as $533, with investors asking company management if things are as good as they can get.

headline: Amphenol forecasts strong quarter as AI, datacom demand lifts sales
summary: Amphenol forecast fourth-quarter results above Wall Street estimates on Wednesday, driven by a strong demand for its products such as cables, sensors and antennas, sending its shares up 9% before the bell. The upbeat results follow continued momentum in AI-related infrastructure spending by technology and defense firms, which has created sustained demand for the company. The Connecticut-based company reported total third-quarter sales of $6.2 billion, beating analysts' estimates of $5.53 billion compiled by LSEG.

headline: Amphenol (NYSE:APH) Reports Strong Q3, Stock Soars
summary: Electrical connector manufacturer Amphenol (NYSE:APH) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 53.4% year on year to $6.19 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($6.05 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 6.1% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.93 per share was 16.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
